About
Set in one of Dubai's most vibrant residential areas Dubai Marina is spread over a 3.5Km canal. Comprising of 500 sheltered berthing spaces Dubai Marina is the largest Marina in the Middle East. A prestigious 5 Gold Anchor Award winning marina recognised for the quality of services and facilities. Also winner of Boat Owner Middle East Awards Leading Marina, 2013. Dubai Marina Yacht Club has become both a Waterfront Destination for residents and tourists alike and a Boaters Haven.

The area

Address
Neighborhood: The Marina
It’s hard to believe that only a decade ago there was no marina. Opened in 2003, the man-made marina runs along a 3km stretch of shoreline. A heady mix of luxurious hotels, apartment buildings, and cafes, the marina hosts regular community events and markets, and is a wonderful place to while away an afternoon or evening. Spectacular at night when the skyscrapers glisten, here you can enjoy dinner on the beach next to the sea, or visit a high-rise bar in a hotel for a magnificent view across the Gulf and the man-made Palm Island, with the world-famous Atlantis Hotel at its end. The Walk at Jumeirah beach Residences is a pedestrianized stretch leading to a new development: The Beach. It’s one of the few places where Gulf nationals mix with tourists and Western ex-pats. It’s a popular place to show off your supercar for an evening, so watch out for Lamborghinis, Maseratis, and Ferraris in abundance.

Thank you Optimal Yachts
Sep 2024 • Friends
I booked the 3hr+ voyage seeing the sights of Dubai. I found Optimal Yachts randomly on Facebook while searching Dubai. I visited with 8 friends all couples and we went for voyage to sit back and chill and take in the sights….. Wow doesn’t cut it, the Yacht was absolutely stunning, having never been to Dubai before or having been on a yacht we were all blown away it was beautiful. The staff were also amazing and really knowledgeable. I initially messaged Optimal Yachts on Facebook and then gave them a call to confirm dates and got through to Leighton. What a guy he is so full of positive energy he delivered what he said was included and even chucked in an extra bottle. The tour was about 3.5hrs and the crew were kind enough to allow us to snorkel and take photos. If you’re looking for things to do in Dubai then I highly recommend giving Optimal Yachts a call and asking for Leighton. He didn’t only look after us with the yacht but we also booked some Jet Ski’s through him too. He suggested places to eat, he recommended some nice bars and clubs and some amazing restaurants he couldn’t help us enough. If we go back next year we will definitely book a fishing trip amazing memories.
